{
  "info": {
    "name": "Inventory System",
    "description": "# Inventory Microservices System\n\nA collection of all REST API endpoints for the inventory system, organized by service: Product, Inventory, Order, and API Gateway.\n\n## Variables\n| Variable | Default |\n|---|---|\n| `productUrl` | `http://localhost:8080` |\n| `inventoryUrl` | `http://localhost:8082` |\n| `orderUrl` | `http://localhost:8081` |\n| `gatewayUrl` | `http://localhost:9000` |\n\n## Workflow\n1. **Create Product** → registers a product with an skuCode\n2. **Restock Inventory** → adds stock quantity (product must already exist in product-service)\n3. **Place Order** → validates stock via inventory-service, then creates the order",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "productUrl",   "value": "http://localhost:8080" },
    { "key": "inventoryUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8082" },
    { "key": "orderUrl",     "value": "http://localhost:8081" },
    { "key": "gatewayUrl",   "value": "http://localhost:9000" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Product Service",
      "description": "Endpoints for managing products. Uses MongoDB via Spring Data MongoDB. Runs on port 8080.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Product",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 201 Created\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has an id\", function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property(\"id\");",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set(\"lastSkuCode\", json.skuCode);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "description": "Creates a new product in the catalog.\n\n**Request Body:**\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `name` | String | Yes | Product name |\n| `description` | String | No | Product description |\n| `price` | BigDecimal | Yes | Unit price (e.g. 999.99) |\n| `skuCode` | String | Yes | Stock keeping unit code (used to link with inventory) |\n\n**Response:** 201 Created — returns the created product with generated MongoDB `id`.",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"iPhone 15\",\n  \"description\": \"Apple iPhone 15 128GB\",\n  \"price\": 799.99,\n  \"skuCode\": \"iphone_15\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{productUrl}}/api/product",
              "host": ["{{productUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "product"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List All Products",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test(\"Response is an array\", function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.be.an(\"array\");",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "description": "Returns all products in the catalog.\n\n**Response:** 200 OK — list of `ProductResponse` objects, each containing `id`, `skuCode`, `name`, `description`, `price`.",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{productUrl}}/api/product",
              "host": ["{{productUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "product"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Inventory Service",
      "description": "Endpoints for managing stock levels. Uses PostgreSQL with Spring Data JPA + Flyway. Runs on port 8082.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Check Stock",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "description": "Checks whether a product has sufficient stock for the requested quantity. Validates that the product exists in product-service first (returns 404 if not found).\n\n**Query Parameters:**\n| Param | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `skuCode` | String | Yes | Product SKU code |\n| `quantity` | Integer | Yes | Desired quantity to check |\n\n**Response:** 200 OK — `true` if stock is sufficient, `false` otherwise.\n**Errors:** 404 if product does not exist.",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{inventoryUrl}}/api/inventory?skuCode=iphone_15&quantity=1",
              "host": ["{{inventoryUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "inventory"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "skuCode",  "value": "iphone_15", "description": "Product SKU to check" },
                { "key": "quantity", "value": "1",          "description": "Number of units to check" }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Restock Inventory",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test(\"Quantity increased\", function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.quantity).to.be.at.least(pm.variables.get(\"restockAmount\"));",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "description": "Adds stock to an existing inventory record. Validates that the product exists in product-service first. Only increases quantity (does not replace).\n\n**Path Parameter:**\n| Param | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `skuCode` | String | Product SKU to restock |\n\n**Request Body:**\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `quantity` | Integer | Yes | Amount to add (must be > 0) |\n\n**Response:** 200 OK — returns updated inventory record.\n**Errors:** 404 if product or SKU not found, 400 if quantity ≤ 0.",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"quantity\": 50\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{inventoryUrl}}/api/inventory/iphone_15/restock",
              "host": ["{{inventoryUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "inventory", "iphone_15", "restock"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List All Inventory",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test(\"Response is an array\", function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an(\"array\");",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "description": "Returns all inventory records with their skuCode and current quantity.\n\n**Response:** 200 OK — array of inventory objects: `[{id, skuCode, quantity}, ...]`.",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{inventoryUrl}}/api/inventory/all",
              "host": ["{{inventoryUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "inventory", "all"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Order Service",
      "description": "Endpoint for placing orders. Uses PostgreSQL + OpenFeign to validate stock with inventory-service. Runs on port 8081.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Place Order",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 201 Created\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test(\"Response confirms order\", function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.include(\"Order placed successfully\");",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "description": "Places a new order. Before creating, the order-service calls inventory-service via OpenFeign to validate stock. If stock is insufficient, returns a 500 error with `\"<skuCode> is not in stock\"`.\n\n**Request Body:**\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `skuCode` | String | Yes | Product SKU to order |\n| `price` | BigDecimal | Yes | Price per unit |\n| `quantity` | Integer | Yes | Number of units to order |\n\n**Response:** 201 Created — `\"Order placed successfully\"` (plain text).\n**Errors:** 500 if stock is insufficient (checked via inventory-service Feign client).",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"skuCode\": \"iphone_15\",\n  \"price\": 799.99,\n  \"quantity\": 1\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{orderUrl}}/api/order",
              "host": ["{{orderUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "order"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "API Gateway",
      "description": "Spring Cloud Gateway Server MVC. Routes requests to the appropriate backend service. Runs on port 9000.\n\nAll requests below go through the gateway, which then forwards them to the actual service. Use these for an end-to-end test of the full system.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Monitoring & Health",
          "description": "Actuator endpoints for monitoring gateway health, circuit breaker state, and system metrics.",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "All Endpoints",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                      "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "description": "Lists all available actuator endpoints exposed by the gateway.\n\n**Response:** 200 OK — JSON object with `_links` containing all available actuator paths (health, circuitbreakers, metrics, etc.).",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/actuator",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["actuator"]
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Health Check",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                      "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                      "});",
                      "pm.test(\"Overall status is UP\", function () {",
                      "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                      "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql(\"UP\");",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "description": "Returns the overall health of the gateway, including circuit breaker status.\n\n**Response:** 200 OK — JSON with `status: \"UP\"` (or `\"DOWN\"` if unhealthy), plus per-component details (circuitBreakers, etc.).",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/actuator/health",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["actuator", "health"]
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Circuit Breaker — List All",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                      "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                      "});",
                      "pm.test(\"Response contains circuit breakers\", function () {",
                      "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                      "    pm.expect(json.circuitBreakers).to.exist;",
                      "    pm.expect(json.circuitBreakers).to.be.an(\"object\");",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "description": "Returns the state and metrics of all circuit breakers.\n\n**Response:** 200 OK — JSON with `circuitBreakers` object containing each named breaker's:\n- `state`: `CLOSED`, `OPEN`, `HALF_OPEN`, or `FORCED_OPEN`\n- `failureRate`: percentage of failed calls\n- `numberOfBufferedCalls`: calls in the sliding window\n- `numberOfFailedCalls`, `numberOfSuccessfulCalls`, etc.\n\n**Circuit opens at:** 50% failure rate, min 5 calls in sliding window of 10.",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/actuator/circuitbreakers",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["actuator", "circuitbreakers"]
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Circuit Breaker — Events",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                      "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                      "});",
                      "pm.test(\"Response is an array\", function () {",
                      "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().circuitBreakerEvents).to.be.an(\"array\");",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "description": "Returns recent circuit breaker state change events (OPEN → HALF_OPEN → CLOSED transitions, error/success events).\n\n**Response:** 200 OK — JSON with `circuitBreakerEvents` array of events, each containing `circuitBreakerName`, `type` (STATE_TRANSITION, ERROR, SUCCESS, etc.), `creationTime`, and `elapsedDuration`.",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/actuator/circuitbreakers/events",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["actuator", "circuitbreakers", "events"]
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Metrics — HTTP Requests",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                      "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "description": "Returns metrics for HTTP server requests processed by the gateway.\n\n**Response:** 200 OK — JSON with `measurements` array containing COUNT, TOTAL_TIME, MAX.",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/actuator/metrics/http.server.requests",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["actuator", "metrics", "http.server.requests"]
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Fallback",
          "description": "Fallback endpoints for handling requests when services are unavailable.",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Service Unavailable (503)",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status is 503 Service Unavailable\", function () {",
                      "    pm.response.to.have.status(503);",
                      "});",
                      "pm.test(\"Body is 'Service Unavailable'\", function () {",
                      "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.eql(\"Service Unavailable\");",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "description": "Returns a 503 Service Unavailable response. This is a static fallback route that does not depend on any backend service.\n\n**Use case:** When the circuit breaker opens for product-service, or when external systems need to detect gateway availability with a known health-check endpoint.\n\n**Response:** 503 Service Unavailable\n**Body:** `\"Service Unavailable\"`",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/fallbackRoute",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["fallbackRoute"]
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Circuit Breaker — Trigger (Product Service Down)",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Response received\", function () {",
                      "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([500, 503]);",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "description": "**Run this multiple times** (via Collection Runner with iteration count ≥ 10) when product-service is **NOT running**.\n\nThis triggers the circuit breaker to open after:\n- 5 minimum calls in the sliding window (size 10)\n- 50% failure rate\n\nOnce the circuit opens, all subsequent requests to `/api/product` will fast-fail immediately with a 503 (or gateway error) instead of waiting for the downstream timeout.\n\n**Check the circuit state** after running: use the `Circuit Breaker — List All` endpoint — expect `state: \"OPEN\"`.",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/api/product",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "product"]
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Product Service",
          "description": "Gateway routes to product-service. Path prefix `/api/product` → `http://localhost:8080`.",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Create Product",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status is 201 Created\", function () {",
                      "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                      "});",
                      "pm.test(\"Response has an id\", function () {",
                      "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                      "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property(\"id\");",
                      "    pm.collectionVariables.set(\"lastSkuCode\", json.skuCode);",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "description": "Creates a new product through the API gateway. The gateway forwards the request to product-service at port 8080.\n\nSame request body as the direct Product Service endpoint.",
                "header": [
                  { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"iPhone 15\",\n  \"description\": \"Apple iPhone 15 128GB\",\n  \"price\": 799.99,\n  \"skuCode\": \"iphone_15\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/api/product",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "product"]
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "List All Products",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                      "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                      "});",
                      "pm.test(\"Response is an array\", function () {",
                      "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                      "    pm.expect(json).to.be.an(\"array\");",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "description": "Lists all products through the API gateway. Gateway forwards to product-service.",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/api/product",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "product"]
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Inventory Service",
          "description": "Gateway routes to inventory-service. Path prefix `/api/inventory` → `http://localhost:8082`.",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Check Stock",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                      "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "description": "Checks stock through the API gateway. Gateway forwards to inventory-service.",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/api/inventory?skuCode=iphone_15&quantity=1",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "inventory"],
                  "query": [
                    { "key": "skuCode",  "value": "iphone_15" },
                    { "key": "quantity", "value": "1" }
                  ]
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Restock Inventory",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                      "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "PUT",
                "description": "Restocks inventory through the API gateway.",
                "header": [
                  { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"quantity\": 50\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/api/inventory/iphone_15/restock",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "inventory", "iphone_15", "restock"]
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "List All Inventory",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", function () {",
                      "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                      "});",
                      "pm.test(\"Response is an array\", function () {",
                      "    pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an(\"array\");",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "description": "Lists all inventory records through the API gateway.",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/api/inventory/all",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "inventory", "all"]
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Order Service",
          "description": "Gateway routes to order-service. Path prefix `/api/order` → `http://localhost:8081`.",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Place Order",
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test(\"Status is 201 Created\", function () {",
                      "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                      "});",
                      "pm.test(\"Response confirms order\", function () {",
                      "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.include(\"Order placed successfully\");",
                      "});"
                    ],
                    "type": "text/javascript"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "description": "Places an order through the API gateway. The gateway forwards to order-service, which then calls inventory-service internally via Feign to validate stock.",
                "header": [
                  { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"skuCode\": \"iphone_15\",\n  \"price\": 799.99,\n  \"quantity\": 1\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/api/order",
                  "host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "order"]
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
